    "actor_description": "Something in front of me is too large to fit in my usual thoughts. My breath catches. I go quiet, not out of fear, but because words feel small and late. For a moment I can only stare, trying to take it in without breaking it.",
    "description_text": "{actor} stills mid-motion, eyes wide and fixed; their mouth parts slightly as if language has fallen away, posture held in a quiet, transfixed awe.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a sudden silence—someone's breath caught and held, like they're witnessing something that demands attention."
    },
